translations: adj.陌生的；不可思议的；奇怪的；没看惯的

phrs.translation: 没看惯的, 陌生的, 哥伦比亚国家标准, 不可思议的
不连接的, 不联结的

sentences.sentence: But experience suggests that an apparently co-operative Iran can be trickier to cope with than an obviously unco-operative one.
sentences.translation: 但是过去的经验表明，一个明显愿意合作的伊朗比一个明显不愿意合作的伊朗更难对付。

sentences.sentence: Fears that unco-ordinated financial regulation could undermine the fragile economic recovery sparked a crisis of confidence among investors.
sentences.translation: 有关金融监管不协调可能破坏脆弱经济复苏的担忧，引发了投资者的信心危机。

sentences.sentence: TIM GEITHNER has reportedly grown so exasperated with unco-operative regulators that he recently blasted them with an expletive-filled rant.
sentences.translation: 提姆·盖特纳据说已被不愿配合的监管者气得七窍生烟，以致他最近措辞严厉地对他们进行猛烈炮轰。
